- Yeah.

16:41.292 --> 16:44.125
Thankyou, mariposa.
Appreciate it.

16:44.195 --> 16:46.925
- Hey, what's happening here?
- Bus fare.

16:46.998 --> 16:49.523
- What aboutyour car?
I thoughtyou had some wheels.
- Spark plugs.

16:49.601 --> 16:52.399
- Spark plugs cost two bucks.
- My dad rebuilt the engine.

16:52.470 --> 16:57.407
The ignition system is shot. Plugs won't fit
until I rebuild the system from scratch.

16:57.475 --> 17:00.933
From scratch? Sounds likeyou
and your pop had a lot in common.

17:01.012 --> 17:03.105
Changing the subject.
What did you find out about Desantos?

17:03.181 --> 17:06.207
I checked around. He's a distributor
for one ofthe drug cartels.

17:06.284 --> 17:08.218
He's not a major player,
but he's got some firepower.

17:08.286 --> 17:11.847
- Any chance we can nudge
the F.B.I. to pick him up?
- [ Chuckles ]

17:11.923 --> 17:13.857
Your little F.B.I. surveillance team...

17:13.925 --> 17:16.951
is more interested in your romp
at the convention than doing you favors, F.Y.I.

17:17.028 --> 17:20.589
It sounds like they've been trying to make
a case against Desantos, but nothing sticks.

17:20.665 --> 17:23.065
- You know how these guys are.
- Who's Desantos's lawyer?

17:23.134 --> 17:25.125
- Gellman.
- Who?

17:25.203 --> 17:27.797
Oh, that's right. You've been running
around the world for the past decade.

17:27.872 --> 17:30.670
Bruce Gellman. He's the lawyer
for the whole drug cartel...

17:30.742 --> 17:34.678
- from Desantos all the way up to eljefe.
- Guess I better meet Gellman.

17:37.815 --> 17:40.613
- What is this? Weapon?
- Nothing you need to worry about.

17:40.685 --> 17:43.279
You know what I worry about?
I worry about mywaitress.

17:43.354 --> 17:46.755
- Howlong this takes, Michael, a week now?
- I'm working on it.

17:46.824 --> 17:51.921
Things got a little complicated, but I think
I've found someone Desantos will listen to.

17:53.264 --> 17:55.892
[ Michael Narrating]
I love commuters.

17:55.967 --> 17:58.458
Anybodywho drives the same
route to work every day...

17:58.536 --> 18:00.470
it's like they're doing
all the work foryou.

18:00.538 --> 18:05.908
And a punctual commuter, a guy who's in
the same place every morning at 8:36 a.m.?

18:05.977 --> 18:09.208
It's almost too easy.

18:10.782 --> 18:14.513
I'm gonna feel really bad
ifyou don't have a Triple "A " card.

18:14.585 --> 18:16.576
I s this a robbery?

18:18.690 --> 18:21.488
The wallet, keys are in the car.

18:21.559 --> 18:24.084
Is this the Seven series,
with the leather seats?

18:24.162 --> 18:27.325
- Tempting, but it needs new tires.
I'm here on business.
- Business?

18:27.398 --> 18:30.799
I've been calling and calling, trying to make
an appointment, maybe getyou on the phone.

18:30.868 --> 18:33.996
Then I thought, "He's a busy man.
I'll just talk to him on his way into work."

18:34.072 --> 18:36.472
- What do you want?
- Alvaro Desantos.

18:36.541 --> 18:39.374
I want to talk to you
about his assault trial.

18:39.444 --> 18:43.744
And my daughterwants a pony.
I don't discuss my clients' business.

18:43.815 --> 18:48.309
A pony. That's funny.
Well, I'll do all the talking then.

18:48.386 --> 18:50.820
I don't know how much attention
you've been paying toyour client lately...

18:50.888 --> 18:52.822
but he's been a bad boy.

18:52.890 --> 18:55.415
Witness intimidation,
attempted murder.

18:55.493 --> 18:57.825
You know, the kind ofthings...

18:57.895 --> 19:01.991
that could cause problems
foryour... other clients.

19:02.066 --> 19:04.660
You have no idea
whoyou're dealing with.

19:04.736 --> 19:08.399
No, I read the article, most of it anyway.
Scary guys, drugs, guns.

19:08.473 --> 19:11.874
I miss something?
I doubt eljefe back in Colombia...

19:11.943 --> 19:16.107
wants to riskyet another murder investigation
just so Desantos can avoid a fewyears in prison.

19:16.180 --> 19:20.617
Have eljefe tell Desantos
to back off.

19:20.685 --> 19:23.552
I want an answerbytomorrow.

19:23.621 --> 19:26.749
I'll meet you here, same time.
Understood?

19:26.824 --> 19:30.385
Oh, I understand.

19:34.832 --> 19:38.768
How'd it go? Gellman gonna talk
to Colombia, make our lives easy?

19:38.836 --> 19:41.737
Hope so. Those two can only stay in
my mom's garage for so long.

19:41.806 --> 19:45.537
- And ifhe doesn't go for it?
- Then ourlives aren't so easy.

19:45.610 --> 19:48.443
There's your man.

19:51.182 --> 19:54.743
Whoa. Been a while.
He's lost a little--a lot ofhair.

19:54.819 --> 19:56.980
I tailed him foryou.

19:57.055 --> 19:59.751
He's renting a nice Mercedes.

19:59.824 --> 20:02.452
Spends a lot of time in restaurants.
He lives pretty well for a spy.

20:02.527 --> 20:05.587
Hands out bribes mostly--
bid rigging, industrial espionage.

20:05.663 --> 20:09.793
I need you to keep watching him. Let me know
when's the best time to get next to him.

20:09.867 --> 20:12.233
- What then?
- What then?

20:12.303 --> 20:14.464
Then I'll find out
who's behind this burn--

20:14.539 --> 20:17.440
'Cause I'm just curious
aboutyour plans.

20:17.508 --> 20:20.170
I suppose ifyou get this resolved,
then you'll leave Miami.

20:20.244 --> 20:23.441
Fi, can we talk about this later?

20:33.825 --> 20:36.521
[Michael Narrating]
Threaten anyserious criminal organization...

20:36.594 --> 20:38.528
and they're going to do
one oftwo things--

20:38.596 --> 20:42.088
[ Whistling ]

20:42.166 --> 20:44.930
They'll send someone
to make a deal...

20:45.002 --> 20:47.436
or they'll send someone
to make a corpse.

20:47.505 --> 20:50.872
Either way, you've got
something to work with.

20:53.444 --> 20:55.674
[ Whistling Continues ]

21:05.756 --> 21:09.852
Problem with the detonator?
I borrowed this when you went to take a leak.

21:12.463 --> 21:14.363
[ Groans ]

21:14.432 --> 21:16.730
Gellman's not coming, is he?

21:18.236 --> 21:20.830
- What's going on?
- I don't know nothing.

21:20.905 --> 21:25.205
Come on. Don't be so modest. You hear
things around the water cooler at the office.

21:27.545 --> 21:30.207
I could take the other knee out
ifthat helps.

21:30.281 --> 21:32.442
They talked to the guys in Colombia.

21:32.517 --> 21:35.816
They say to kill you all.

21:35.887 --> 21:37.878
Really?

21:41.926 --> 21:44.224
That's not what
I was hoping they'd say.

21:50.334 --> 21:52.598
What?
We have to leave Miami?

21:52.670 --> 21:55.195
You don't have a choice.
The whole cartel is afteryou now.

21:55.273 --> 21:57.503
- Theywon't stop until you're dead.
- Well, what aboutyou?

21:57.575 --> 22:02.342
- They don't care about me. I'm just in theirway.
- So we just leave? That's it?

22:02.413 --> 22:04.381
Sophie, he'sjust trying to help us.

22:04.448 --> 22:07.212
It was bad enough being stuck in here,
but now we're just supposed to leave?

22:07.285 --> 22:10.686
What about my friends?
It's my-- It's my senioryear.

22:10.755 --> 22:12.347
I have a date forthe dance.

22:12.423 --> 22:15.915
Perimeter's clear.
Sam's out front keeping a lookout.

22:15.993 --> 22:18.154
Can't you do something?

22:18.229 --> 22:22.063
Didn't you sayyou were better
at tactical whatever than he is?

22:22.133 --> 22:23.964
What? I am.

22:24.035 --> 22:27.368
I'm sure Fi would be happy
to take on the cartel with a lighter...

22:27.438 --> 22:30.464
and whatever's in the liquor cabinet,
but trust me, it's not an option.

22:30.541 --> 22:34.375
- You have to go now.
- Michael, we don't even have our things.

22:34.445 --> 22:36.913
No, they'll have people
watching your house.

22:36.981 --> 22:40.917
But I need myphone.
It has all myfriends'numbers on it.

22:40.985 --> 22:43.545
Maybe I'm not being clear.

22:43.621 --> 22:46.146
You will leave Miami,
you will not contact anyone.

22:46.224 --> 22:49.387
You will start over.
Theywant Cara and Sophie Stagner dead.

22:49.460 --> 22:52.588
It is ourjob to turn Cara
and Sophie Stagner into ghosts.

23:04.542 --> 23:08.000
I know how you feel.
Normally, I would agree with you.

23:08.079 --> 23:12.573
Michael would change his identity
and disappear to get out of a parking ticket.

23:12.650 --> 23:15.642
But in this case, he's right.

23:16.687 --> 23:18.621
It's for the best.

23:18.689 --> 23:21.249
Okay, so where do we go?

23:21.325 --> 23:24.852
I need you to write up a list--
places you have family, vacation spots...

23:24.929 --> 23:27.090
anywhere you've been
in the last 1 0 years or so.

23:27.164 --> 23:29.496
You can go anywhere
that's not on that list.

23:29.567 --> 23:32.001
Won't theyjust follow us?

23:32.069 --> 23:34.469
Trust me, theywill not know
whereyou're heading.

23:39.243 --> 23:42.041
Fi, we've got to get over
to Cara's apartment now.

23:46.117 --> 23:48.051
[Michael Narrating]
Whenyou go on the run...

23:48.119 --> 23:51.111
the first thingyou do is lay down
tracks in the opposite direction.

23:51.188 --> 23:55.318
But that only works ifthe bad guys
find the trail and believe it's for real--

23:55.393 --> 23:57.361
- [ Cell Phone Rings ]
- which means selling it.

23:57.428 --> 24:01.159
You need to put on a little show,
make them feel clever.

24:01.232 --> 24:03.598
When you make somebody work
to get a piece of information...

24:03.668 --> 24:08.128
they'll believe it that much
more because it's hard to get.

24:08.205 --> 24:10.673
I 'm i n Cara's apartment.
They see me?

24:10.741 --> 24:12.902
Yeah. Hurry up, F.i.

24:12.977 --> 24:16.003
Michael, you worried about me?

24:16.080 --> 24:18.014
That is sweet.

24:18.082 --> 24:20.846
Sometimes I feel like you're more
of a romantic than you realize.

24:20.918 --> 24:22.852
Fi, there are guys
with guns outside.

24:22.920 --> 24:25.388
It's not that bad. Last week I was hauling
in some dodgy meth dealer.

24:25.456 --> 24:28.084
I don't want to hear
aboutyour otherjobs, okay?

24:28.159 --> 24:31.560
Ifl knewyou were going to take this long,
I would have done it myself.

24:31.629 --> 24:34.154
Don't be silly.
You're on their hit list.

24:34.231 --> 24:36.756
-Just hurry.
- Actually, I was thinking that now...

24:36.834 --> 24:40.235
would be a good time to talk toyou
about getting a key toyour place.

24:40.304 --> 24:42.602
- Fiona, please.
- What?

24:42.673 --> 24:47.838
I'm just saying it's practical.
I'm not talking about moving in.

24:47.912 --> 24:50.904
- I couldcome overanytime andwe could--
- Okay, here theycome.

24:50.981 --> 24:52.915
Get out ofthere now.

24:55.820 --> 24:57.549
So what do you think?
Key?

24:59.523 --> 25:02.219
[ Michael]
Two more coming in and Desantos.

25:07.098 --> 25:10.727
- I want an answer.
- F.i,just go to the back door
and get out ofthere now.

25:10.801 --> 25:14.134
- Yes or no?
- F.ine!Just get out ofthere.

25:14.205 --> 25:16.639
Fi! Fiona, get out of there!

25:16.707 --> 25:19.699
Goddamn it, Fi, get out of there!

25:28.519 --> 25:31.647
As far as Desantos
and the Colombians are concerned...

25:31.722 --> 25:34.213
the Stagners are offto Salt Lake City.

25:34.291 --> 25:39.388
You know, Michael, ifI'm gonna be there more,
you really ought to get some proper furniture.

25:41.499 --> 25:44.127
So they thinkwe're going
to Salt Lake City, but we're really--

25:44.201 --> 25:46.795
Going to Buffalo.
Tomorrow morning you're on the first flight.

25:46.871 --> 25:49.305
Airport security is your friend
at a time like this.

25:49.373 --> 25:52.570
- What are we supposed to do in Buffalo?
- Same thing you do here.

25:52.643 --> 25:56.636
There are malls
and... clothing stores.

26:02.620 --> 26:06.021
[ Sighs ]
Such a tough age just to get up and move.

26:06.090 --> 26:10.288
I joined the military at her age. I left home
with 50 bucks and a change of clothes.

26:10.361 --> 26:13.125
Was someone trying to
chaseyou down and kill you?

26:16.700 --> 26:20.158
- [ Cell Phone Rings ]
- I'll, uh-- I'll talk toyou in the morning.

26:20.237 --> 26:21.761
Yeah, Fi?

26:21.839 --> 26:25.935
Your Egyptian just got back
and he has dinner reservations.

26:26.010 --> 26:28.376
[Michael]
I'll be right there.

26:30.347 --> 26:32.941
[Michael Narrating]
Approaching a spyin the middle ofajob...

26:33.017 --> 26:35.076
gives you a lot ofleverage.

26:35.152 --> 26:37.950
They're playing a delicate game,
and the last thing they want...

26:38.022 --> 26:41.958
is someone coming in and smashing
their delicate game with a brick.

26:42.026 --> 26:43.857
Good to see you, Akhom.

26:43.928 --> 26:47.329
Good to seeyou, Michael,
my old friend.

26:47.398 --> 26:50.128
- Why,just the other day, I was telling someone--
- Michael.

26:50.201 --> 26:52.169
how you saved my life.

26:52.236 --> 26:55.000
It's good to see you.
I 'm in a meeting. Maybe later.

26:55.072 --> 26:58.974
I need a few minutes with him, guys.
You don't mind, do you?

27:02.880 --> 27:05.348
- What do you want?
- I need your help.

27:05.416 --> 27:09.352
Akhom, ifit wasn't forme,
you'd be buriedsomewhere in the desert...

27:09.420 --> 27:11.888
a horror story diplomats tell one another
around the campfire...

27:11.956 --> 27:13.890
but you're not because I helped you.

27:13.958 --> 27:16.688
I'm grateful.
But you're burned. You're out.

27:16.760 --> 27:19.320
You're still in business, though.

27:19.396 --> 27:22.297
Wasn't that the vice chair
ofthe Sudanese delegation?

27:22.366 --> 27:25.597
And what is that?
That is-- Oh.

27:25.669 --> 27:28.069
- What doyou want?
- Well, for starters, a sip ofyour drink.

27:28.138 --> 27:31.130
I mean, the taste is just-- Oh.

27:31.208 --> 27:36.111
Oh, and a copy ofthe Homeland Security
directive that authorized my burn notice.

27:36.180 --> 27:38.774
- [ Scoffs ] I can't.
- Sure, you can.

27:38.849 --> 27:41.511
Becauseyou don't want me
to tell your friends there...

27:41.585 --> 27:46.181
about thejobsyou did
on the wrong side ofhis border.

27:46.257 --> 27:48.953
Maybe he'll forgive you.

27:49.026 --> 27:51.187
[ Cell Phone: Dance Music ]

27:51.262 --> 27:54.925
Yeah, I need an answer... now.

27:56.700 --> 27:58.964
I also need your valet ticket.

28:00.504 --> 28:01.971
- Michael!
- What happened? Where is she?

28:02.039 --> 28:04.507
She's gone.
The alarm went off and--

28:04.575 --> 28:07.237
How many men were there,
and did you get a look at their car?

28:07.311 --> 28:10.803
What? No, there was nobody.
She snuck out while I was asleep.

28:10.881 --> 28:14.817
- It's her spring formal.
- Sam, I need you to get to the safe house.

28:14.885 --> 28:18.946
-Just let me put on some pants.
- Come naked.Just get here now.

28:19.023 --> 28:22.254
Mike, ifthey find Sophie,
they're gonna--

28:22.326 --> 28:25.318
Hey, I'll find her first.

28:36.167 --> 28:38.294
[ Chattering ]

28:40.237 --> 28:42.262
Sophie.

28:42.339 --> 28:45.172
- Sophie.
- Oh, come on.

28:45.242 --> 28:47.335
- [ Vehicle Approaches ]
- Come on.

28:47.411 --> 28:51.438
[ Sophie ] One night. Why?
Why can'tyoujust leave me alone?

28:54.185 --> 28:58.144
One night, that's all I wanted.
But you have to be a drama queen.

28:58.222 --> 29:00.622
Why can'tyoujust leave me alone?
I don't understand.

29:00.691 --> 29:03.922
- Oh, my God. Oh, my God!
- Shop class, where is it?

29:07.131 --> 29:09.531
- Turn the lights back on.
- But they'll find us.

29:09.600 --> 29:12.296
We're not hiding.

29:16.440 --> 29:19.705
You will go out the back door.
You're gonna meet me behind the gym...

29:19.777 --> 29:21.938
and I will find you in five minutes.

29:23.881 --> 29:25.940
- Seriously, go.
- I can't.

29:26.016 --> 29:29.952
- No arguments. Go. Sophie! Go right now.
- You can't leave me!

29:30.020 --> 29:34.548
I won't let anything
bad happen toyou. Go. Go.

29:45.803 --> 29:48.237
[ Screaming ]

29:54.612 --> 29:59.311
[Michael Narrating] Basic rule ofbodyguarding:
Neverfight with the protectee around...

29:59.383 --> 30:03.752
mostlybecause ifthey happen to catch
a stray bullet, youjust lostyourjob.

30:16.467 --> 30:19.061
Sophie?

30:19.136 --> 30:21.195
Sophie?

30:21.272 --> 30:24.799
Sophie, bad guys gone now.
Sophe?

30:31.115 --> 30:34.516
I should have listened toyou.
I'm sorry.

30:34.585 --> 30:36.849
Let's go.

30:39.557 --> 30:41.752
I barely had a chance to go inside.

30:44.762 --> 30:47.356
I didn't even have a chance
to say good-bye to my boyfriend.

30:47.431 --> 30:49.956
Boyfriend? I thought
he was just a date.

30:50.034 --> 30:52.400
He could have been my boyfriend.

30:54.104 --> 30:56.937
I'll never know now.

30:59.543 --> 31:02.706
I was on this job once in Dublin.

31:02.780 --> 31:06.409
The whole plan fell apart,
totally compromised.

31:06.483 --> 31:08.644
I only had an hour
to get out ofthe country.

31:08.719 --> 31:12.280
I couldn't get word back to
a key asset I had developed in the I.R.A.

31:19.630 --> 31:25.000
It was Fiona.
We were involved romantically.

31:25.069 --> 31:28.038
Areyou guys still together?

31:28.105 --> 31:31.506
No. But we reconnected later.

31:34.945 --> 31:38.346
Sort of.
Sophie, we should go.

31:38.415 --> 31:43.011
Soyou're saying that ifwe're meant
to be together, that we'll find each other?

31:43.087 --> 31:45.021
Sure.

31:47.458 --> 31:50.188
- You're really bad at this.
- Yeah.

31:52.596 --> 31:55.326
It's just hard, you know?

31:57.001 --> 31:59.993
Leaveyourwhole life behind.

32:02.339 --> 32:05.240
Sometimes it can be.

32:07.244 --> 32:09.178
Yeah.

32:11.582 --> 32:13.914
Can we go now?

32:21.759 --> 32:24.887
Bottom line is,
Desantos knows Cara hasn't left.

32:24.962 --> 32:27.988
Eventually, he'll hunt her down.
We need a more permanent solution.

32:28.065 --> 32:30.397
- It's about time.
- Fi.

32:30.467 --> 32:33.595
Sam, haveyou talked to
your F.B.I. buddies lately?

32:33.671 --> 32:36.196
Guys, we've been through this, all right?
They're not my buddies.

32:36.273 --> 32:38.332
- They're--They're just--
- Your keepers?

32:38.409 --> 32:40.809
- Your master?
- That's enough out ofyou.

32:40.878 --> 32:43.210
They're both by-the-book suits, right?

32:48.118 --> 32:51.884
Well, yeah, Mike, they're feds.
I mean, come on.

32:51.956 --> 32:54.550
Why?

32:54.625 --> 32:56.991
[ Michael Narrating]
Modern technologyhas made it possible...

32:57.061 --> 33:01.725
to do sophisticated electronic surveillance
with stufffrom your local electronics store.

33:01.799 --> 33:04.734
It sounds more fun than it is.

33:26.023 --> 33:28.583
- You've come for that drink?
- Another time.

33:28.659 --> 33:30.854
This has gone far enough.
We want to make a deal.

33:30.928 --> 33:34.557
Good. Fine.
Bring me the girl, we make a deal.

33:34.631 --> 33:36.997
Just listen to this first.

33:40.104 --> 33:43.972
Who is this?

33:44.041 --> 33:49.104
Uh, yes, Mr. Desantos. Uh, this is Chuck Finley,
attorney for Cara Stagner.

33:49.179 --> 33:52.410
Mr. Finley, hey, I dislike meetings
over the telephone.

33:52.483 --> 33:54.781
Perhaps I could meet
with your client face-to-face.

33:54.852 --> 33:59.152
Well, I just want to tell you that
Cara Stagner is not going to be a problem.

33:59.223 --> 34:00.952
Not a problem?

34:01.025 --> 34:04.927
You see, this confuses me because I know
she made a statement to the police.

34:04.995 --> 34:07.293
Yes, uh, and to the feds.

34:07.364 --> 34:10.060
But, uh, they turned her away.

34:10.134 --> 34:14.230
She thought they would, uh,
put her in witness protection?

34:14.304 --> 34:17.739
-Well, she doesn't want to die.
-And I don't want to go to jail.

34:17.808 --> 34:20.777
So, this is our dilemma.

34:20.844 --> 34:22.607
How can I convince you?

34:22.679 --> 34:24.772
I want a guarantee.

34:24.848 --> 34:28.340
I have to know that
she's not going to testify....

34:28.418 --> 34:31.286
and the only way I can know
this for sure is, uh--

34:31.355 --> 34:33.983
Let me tell you how we do this
in Colombia, hey?

34:36.326 --> 34:39.295
[ Michael Narrating]
F.aking surveillance video has come a long way.

34:39.362 --> 34:43.629
It used to beyou'd spend days slaving
over a VHS tape with a razor blade.

34:43.699 --> 34:46.260
Now it's a few hours on a computer.

34:46.335 --> 34:51.137
I don't want to go to jail.
To testify., I want witness protection.

34:51.208 --> 34:55.007
I want a guarantee.
Do you really think you can hide me?

34:55.079 --> 34:57.445
I've heard legit recordings
a hell of a lot worse.

34:57.514 --> 35:00.278
Just add in a little car noise, it'll sound
like a surveillancevan across the street.

35:00.350 --> 35:03.547
- Haveyou talked to the feds yet?
- Mmm, yeah.

35:03.620 --> 35:05.520
They're all over it.

35:05.589 --> 35:09.685
And they're still asking aboutyour little,
um, Developing Nations escapade.

35:09.760 --> 35:13.628
But when they think I'm gonna
give 'em somethin' good, they buy me lunch.

35:16.366 --> 35:21.360
Anyway, he was looking for someone
he used to know, like, uh, an old spy buddy.

35:21.438 --> 35:24.236
I mean, between you and me,
I think he's lonely.

35:24.308 --> 35:27.471
I couldn't get more out ofhim,
but I think he's a sixpack awayfrom talkin'.

